The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Robber let off

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: A man who allegedly waved a knife at a local priest and ran away with a temple donation box has been acquitted by the Supreme Court because he did not have a lawyer to defend him, reports our legal correspondent. 

 Under Section 304, a sessions court has to assign an accused a lawyer at the expense of the state to defend him during trial if he does not have the means to hire one. 




